Response ID: resp_192
Response Text: I think you might have a grant available for venues that potentially could result in the following, but I would love to see an effort to get more diverse identities into positions of power in the music industry. The vast majority of venues, studios, labels, and businesses are owned by men by a landslide. So, you can throw an event somewhere and try and build culture from the ground up, but a lot of people get stuck from top-down pressures. Ultimately, people in ownership and leadership positions are still calling the shots. So, if we really want to change the culture around here, we need some representation at the top too. So, this means helping underrepresented communities create and/or run venues, music studios, creative or cultural spaces, and other music-related businesses or organizations. But maybe the first step for the previous idea is providing resources especially in business knowledge to these folks to keep everything sustainable and manageable, perhaps securing mentorship with more established businesses/orgs.

